  "body": "Added comments as below.\r\nTwo questions:\r\n 1) shall we properly announce remove pending when tx pool reaches limit\r\n 2) if block producer removes the transaction from the pool and then the transaction is received again, what happens?\r\n 3) if the transaction is losing to higher gas price transactions and then it is received again when the pool is empty then is the hash cache preventing us from adding it back?\r\n   \r\n        /// <summary>\r\n        /// A transaction that has been pending has been removed from the pool.\r\n        /// This can happen if the transaction has been picked for block construction by the block producer\r\n        /// or has been seen in a recently processed block. This is currently not invoked when the transaction\r\n        /// is pushed out by another transaction as the result of cache size limit.\r\n        /// </summary>\r\n        event EventHandler<TxEventArgs> RemovedPending;",
